JOHANNESBURG - Chinese artist and dissident Ai Weiwei  has unveiled an enormous inflatable rubber life raft at Australia’s Sydney Biennale art exhibition to highlight the struggle of migrants Carrying more than 300 supersized anonymous figures, the 60-metre-long artwork is called 'The Law of the Journey'. Watch | Exiled Chinese artist Ai Weiwei's unveils 'refugee boat' in Sydney pic.twitter.com/UnEpPve4CC It is made from the same material as the rafts used to save migrants in the Mediterranean Sea. Thousands of people fleeing Africa and Asia have died while attempting the treacherous journey. READ NEXT: Chinese artist Ai Weiwei to build fences in New York eNCA